response.overview: "The Eurovision Song Contest 1990 was the 35th edition of the annual Eurovision Song Contest. It was held in Zagreb, Yugoslavia on 5 May 1990. The first republican free elections held in Croatia in April and May 1990 was followed by political debate of the ethnic relations between the Croats and the Serbs in SR Croatia. This resulted in The Log Revolution, an insurrection that would escalate into the Croatian War of Independence. Fragments untitled #3 places the event in broader European context." â€” Doplgenger
